[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":549},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F20\u002Fcoffeescript-basics\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F20\u002Fcoffeescript-basics\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F20\u002Fcoffeescript-basics\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F20\u002Fcoffeescript-basics\u002F":524,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F20\u002Fcoffeescript-basics\u002F":533},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20190620\u002F3794703376\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":61,"date":509,"description":510,"extension":511,"lang":512,"meta":513,"navigation":138,"path":514,"readingMinutes":515,"seo":516,"standalone":517,"stem":518,"tags":519,"tldr":521,"updated":509,"url":522,"__hash__":523},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fcoffeescript-basics.md","CoffeeScript Basics: What This Compile-to-JS Language Actually Looks Like","1001219529",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":504},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,41,45,48,55,63,69,84,87,93,96,99,169,175,178,198,203,269,274,302,307,331,336,366,371,416,421,456,461,495,500],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A project might need me to write some CoffeeScript soon, so I figured I'd poke at it a bit and figure out what this thing actually is — and what ways there are to write it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"a-quick-coffeescript-dictionary","A quick CoffeeScript dictionary",[17,25,26],{},"CoffeeScript isn't a new language. A lot of people see the name \"CoffeeScript\" and immediately think \"ugh, another new thing to learn.\" But really, CoffeeScript is just another way of writing JavaScript — it's what's called a transpiled language. Basically that means it gets compiled down into another language, which in this case is JavaScript.",[17,28,29],{},"The language itself was inspired by a handful of others — Haskell, JavaScript, Perl, Python, Ruby, YAML — but mostly JavaScript. So while you're writing it, if you've done any Python or Ruby before, some of it might feel kind of familiar.",[17,31,32,33,40],{},"If you want a clearer picture, go check out the ",[34,35,39],"a",{"href":36,"rel":37},"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FCoffeeScript",[38],"nofollow","Wiki",".",[12,42,44],{"id":43},"getting-started","Getting started",[17,46,47],{},"Like I said, CoffeeScript transpiles into JavaScript, so you're going to need some kind of tool to do that conversion. You can Google \"CoffeeScript tutorial\" and you'll find a few articles on it.",[17,49,50],{},[51,52],"img",{"alt":53,"src":54},"CoffeeScript tutorial","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUIVyCCh.png",[17,56,57,58,62],{},"The first result, \"",[59,60,61],"span",{},"JavaScript"," CoffeeScript basic intro,\" covers how to transpile CoffeeScript into JavaScript. But here I figured I'd do it a different way — with Gulp. So I searched \"CoffeeScript Gulp\" instead (I didn't really want to globally install a bunch of stuff, so I wanted to see if Gulp could pull it off).",[17,64,65],{},[51,66],{"alt":67,"src":68},"CoffeeScript Gulp","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FWWwA3Od.png",[17,70,71,72,77,78,83],{},"The first result mentioned gulp-coffee, so we can just dive right in. I'm going to skip over a lot of the Gulp boilerplate here — if you're not clear on how to write Gulp tasks, check out this series I wrote: ",[34,73,76],{"href":74,"rel":75},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fcategories\u002Fgulp\u002F",[38],"Gulp isn't a drink, it's a task automation tool (article in Mandarin)",". Here's the ",[34,79,82],{"href":80,"rel":81},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FgulpSample",[38],"repo sample"," for that series too.",[17,85,86],{},"So let's quickly install gulp-coffee, set up the folders, all that.",[17,88,89],{},[51,90],{"alt":91,"src":92},"Setting up folders and Gulp","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fnzngzjr.png",[17,94,95],{},"CoffeeScript's syntax is a little different, so let me jot down how you write it.",[17,97,98],{},"Basic stuff first — variable declarations and comments:",[100,101,106],"pre",{"className":102,"code":103,"language":104,"meta":105,"style":105},"language-coffee shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","# This is a single-line comment\n###\nThis is a multi-line comment\n###\n\n# This is how you declare a variable — no var needed\nsayhi = 'Coffee';\nname = 'Hello World';\n\nhello = name + sayhi;\n","coffee","",[107,108,109,116,122,128,133,140,146,152,158,163],"code",{"__ignoreMap":105},[59,110,113],{"class":111,"line":112},"line",1,[59,114,115],{},"# This is a single-line comment\n",[59,117,119],{"class":111,"line":118},2,[59,120,121],{},"###\n",[59,123,125],{"class":111,"line":124},3,[59,126,127],{},"This is a multi-line comment\n",[59,129,131],{"class":111,"line":130},4,[59,132,121],{},[59,134,136],{"class":111,"line":135},5,[59,137,139],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":138},true,"\n",[59,141,143],{"class":111,"line":142},6,[59,144,145],{},"# This is how you declare a variable — no var needed\n",[59,147,149],{"class":111,"line":148},7,[59,150,151],{},"sayhi = 'Coffee';\n",[59,153,155],{"class":111,"line":154},8,[59,156,157],{},"name = 'Hello World';\n",[59,159,161],{"class":111,"line":160},9,[59,162,139],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":138},[59,164,166],{"class":111,"line":165},10,[59,167,168],{},"hello = name + sayhi;\n",[17,170,171],{},[51,172],{"alt":173,"src":174},"The compiled JavaScript","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F3o0iYTn.png",[17,176,177],{},"Next up, writing functions:",[100,179,181],{"className":102,"code":180,"language":104,"meta":105,"style":105},"# Writing a function\na = sayHi2 ->\n  return sayhi + hello;\n",[107,182,183,188,193],{"__ignoreMap":105},[59,184,185],{"class":111,"line":112},[59,186,187],{},"# Writing a function\n",[59,189,190],{"class":111,"line":118},[59,191,192],{},"a = sayHi2 ->\n",[59,194,195],{"class":111,"line":124},[59,196,197],{},"  retur